@hypedrive: @nissan will unveil an electrified R32 Skyline GT-R at the 2025 Tokyo Auto Salon (TAS). After 18 months of development, the iconic "Godzilla" gets a modern EV makeover.⁠
⁠
The original R32, produced between 1989 and 1994, had a 2.6L twin-turbo engine with 276 hp and an advanced all-wheel-drive system. While power and performance details for the EV version aren't revealed yet, it’s part of a trend to retrofit classic cars with electric drivetrains, merging nostalgia with modern tech.⁠
⁠
The “R32EV” will be showcased alongside other Nissan innovations from January 10 to 12.⁠
Photo: Nissan

It's finally 2025 and all many can think about is 'Grand Theft Auto VI.' @rockstargames has managed to stay silent for all of 2024 and we continue to ponder and theorize when will this game actually release. ⁠
⁠
Here's to hoping for that Fall/Winter release but before we jump to that, new reports according to the Financial Times, based on information from video game research group DFC Intelligence have determined the game is set to exceed $1 Billion USD in pre-orders as soon as it launches leading to an estimated $3.2 Billion USD in the first 12 months. Stay tuned for more info.⁠
Photo: Rockstar Games⁠

⁠
The collection features a number of your favorites beginning with the popular AE1 Low in a shimmering iridescent white, Harden Vol. 9, Intimidation Low, Crazy 8 Low, and more. As of January 1, @rolex have hiked up its prices for the US and UK market.⁠
⁠
The GMT-Master II, including the “Pepsi” bezel and the black/gray ceramic variant, now costs $10,800 USD (Oyster bracelet) and $11,000 USD (Jubilee), reflecting a $100 USD hike (0.9%).⁠
⁠
The Daytona saw a more significant increase, rising from $15,100 USD to $15,500 USD (2.6%) in the US, and from £13,200 GBP to £13,600 GBP (3%) in the UK.⁠
⁠
The date-less Oystersteel Submariner now retails at $9,200 USD (1% increase) in the US and £8,100 GBP (0.62%) in the UK.⁠
⁠
Lastly, the Explorer II’s 42mm Oystersteel model rose to $9,750 USD (1%) in the US and £8,550 GBP (0.58%) in the UK.⁠
⁠
Photo: Leon Neal/Getty Images

@bape_us is beginning again — both literally and symbolically — with its Lunar New Year "Year of the Snake" capsule, marking its first in-line release of 2025.⁠
⁠
Celebrating the snake’s symbolism of regrowth and rebirth, the collection embraces transformation through a Yamata-no-Orochi motif, a nod to the mythical creature representing renewal in Japanese mythology.⁠
⁠
The lineup swaps camo for snakeskin, featuring scaly foil-printed graphic tees, a reimagined APE HEAD logo with a circling snake, and pieces like jackets, T-shirts, denim, mesh caps, and hoodies.⁠
⁠
The capsule is vailable now at BAPE's official webstore.⁠
Photo: BAPE
Who do you think had a bigger year? 🧐

@nike is continuing to revitalize its status by bringing back some of the most coveted grails from the vault following the release of the "Wu-Tang" Dunks, "Stash" 95s, and rumors of the return of the original "PlayStation" AF1s, and many more. ⁠
⁠
New images have surfaced showcasing the first retro of the UNDEFEATED Jordan 4s which will feature two types of heel tabs, the classic "Jumpman" iteration and a new "Nike Air" version. Overall, the materials used are the classic nubuck in olive paired with the contrasting orange laces and branding as well as the removable velcro tongue patches.⁠
⁠
Expected to release June 28, these are sure to be on many enthusiast's grail lists.⁠
Photo: @clpro77

We’re officially in 2025, and it’s already off to a strong start, as shown in the latest edition of our product drops series.⁠
⁠
First up is the highly anticipated @louisvuitton x Murakami Re-Edition Collection, celebrating its 20th anniversary with over 200 creations. Also on the collaboration front, there’s @uniqlo’s ‘Dragon Ball DAIMA’ UT capsule, @kith x @new_manual, and more.⁠
⁠
Swipe through for this week’s highlights.⁠
Photo: Courtesy of brands

Despite @champagnepapi having a challenging 2024, the 6 God hopes to gain a couple of Ws moving into the new year and with the help of his NOCTA line including his recent “Pink Foam” AF1s.⁠
⁠
Now, new samples have surfaced of two pairs of OVO x Air Jordan 9s in both black and white. This particular model never saw a retail release (“look-see” samples are prototypes created to visualize and evaluate the look of a silhouette before mass production, and the final retail release can differ from its “look-see” samples), but are very close to the other OVO releases of the era in material and color scheme.⁠
⁠
The white pair boasts a high-gloss leather construction and is adorned with gold accents on its tongue badge, insole and translucent outsole, while the black pair opts for a more muted look with matte leather, an opaque outsole and branded hits split between gold and black. The key detail on both pairs arrives via the aforementioned tongue tag, which swaps out its standard Air Jordan branding for an October’s Very Own text hit. Check out the gallery above.⁠
Photo: Getty Images,@ayeelectric_

@stoneisland is celebrating the Lunar New Year with a special "Year of the Snake '025” Collection.⁠
⁠
As a snake is constantly shedding its skin, it’s become a metaphor for everything from renewal to transformation and spiritual growth — and also represents traits like wisdom, creativity and intuition — so Stone Island has taken the serpentine inspiration and created a versatile collection with details like swooping red stitching and modular, detachable pieces.⁠
⁠
A highlight from the collection includes a signature nylon metal jacket done up with quilted detailing throughout paired with contrast red stitching, detachable sleeves and hood to complete the overall look. Accompanying pieces also include hoodies, sweaters, bags, shirts, and more. ⁠
⁠
The Stone Island “Year of the Snake ‘025” collection is available now via Stone Island’s webstore and brick-and-mortar outposts in the APAC region, and a global release may follow in the coming weeks.⁠
Photo: Stone Island⁠

FBI and New Orleans law enforcement don't believe there were any other suspects involved in the Bourbon Street attack that caused 14 deaths, and injured dozens on New Year's Day. ⁠
⁠
"We do not assess at this point that anyone else is involved in this attack except for Shamsud-Din Jabbar," said Christopher Raia, the deputy assistant director of the FBI's counter-terrorism division, during a Thursday news conference. ⁠
⁠
Click the link in our bio for more updates.⁠
⁠
📝: Caroline Wilburn, Octavia Johnson / Houston Chronicle reporters

At least 10 people died and dozens more were injured Wednesday morning when a truck drove into a crowd in the French Quarter of New Orleans.⁠
⁠
Police have described the attack as intentional, and said the truck's driver opened fired on police after the crash, wounding two officers. The driver, identified as Shamsud Din Jabbar, 42, was killed in a shooting, according to the Times-Picayune newspaper.⁠
⁠
The motives for the attack are unknown. In an early-morning press conference, New Orleans Mayor LaToya Cantrell called the crash a "terrorist attack." The FBI on Wednesday morning said it was investigating the attack as a "act of terrorism."⁠
⁠
Read more at the link in our bio.

As a matter of tradition, January is a reset month for many. The winter holidays and their festive excesses are behind us and resolutions are made to hit the gym, cook at home, cut out booze or to shore up finances.⁠
⁠
Two-thirds of Americans are considering making a financial resolution for 2025, according to an annual survey from Fidelity Investments. In particular, 43% of respondents are resolved to save more money and 31% aim to spend less. ⁠
⁠
Some will even embrace a "buy nothing" challenge in support of those goals.⁠
The concept is not new, but social media has helped popularize it. The Buy Nothing Project, says 1.6 million people around the world have downloaded its app since the project launched in Washington state in 2013. The project's global community, including those who participate on other platforms, comprises 12 million people, it says, and interest in the concept has surged over the past several weeks, according to Google Trends.⁠
⁠
Here's what to know if you're considering a buy-nothing challenge in 2025.⁠
⁠
Click the link in our bio to read more.⁠
⁠
📝: Erica Grieder / Houston Chronicle reporter

Stories such as the Michelin Guide’s arrival in Texas or the rollercoaster ride of events surrounding a Heights bagel shop may have been among the Chronicle’s most read food stories in 2024.⁠
⁠
But between restaurant critic Alison Cook (who recently left an award-winning career in newspaper journalism), a food editor, columnist and reporter, our team has covered a lot more ground.⁠
⁠
We ate our way through Fung’s Kitchen’s lobster mountain and tasting menus at newly minted Michelin-starred restaurants. There were countless meals scouting out the best tacos, pizzas and burgers. Of course, our annual Top 100 restaurants project also required stomachs of steel as we crisscrossed the greater Houston area, from The Woodlands to Kemah.⁠
⁠
As we put together this list of the 10 best new restaurants to open in 2024, however, it goes without saying that it was a tough year for restaurants.⁠
⁠
For these 10 restaurants to stand out is a salute to not only the chefs and restaurateurs, but the restaurant workers who feed Houstonians on a nearly daily basis.⁠
⁠
Click the link in our bio to read more.⁠
⁠
📝: Bao Ong / Houston Chronicle restaurant columnist⁠

Seven Houston companies appear on Forbes's 2024 ranking of the nation's top private companies, with two breaking into the top 100 and one making its first appearance. ⁠
⁠
This year, there were 275 companies on the Forbes list of top private companies. The threshold for inclusion is having at least $2 billion in revenue, Forbes said, and companies are ranked by revenue for the most recently completed fiscal year, which for most would be 2023.⁠
⁠
In Texas, San Antonio-based grocer H-E-B is the largest privately held company, according to Forbes, ranking fifth in the nation with $46.5 billion in revenue last year. ⁠
⁠
Click the link in our bio to read more. ⁠
⁠
✍️: Erica Grieder / Houston Chronicle reporter⁠
📸: Melissa Phillip/ Houston Chronicle photographer

We end the year a little less rich than when we marked the first day of January off our calendars. From political mainstays to sports heroes to culinary giants, 2024 took people who helped shape our city and our state.⁠
⁠
Their advocacy sculpted Houston, their words changed hearts and laws and still managed to make us laugh, and their songs will grace our Spotify playlists for years to come.⁠
⁠
Here are some of the people we lost in 2024.⁠
⁠
Click the link in our bio to read more.⁠
⁠
📝: Sarah Smith / Houston Chronicle reporter

The growth of the Houston region continues to seem nearly inexorable, with two exurbs in the region appearing on a new list of the fastest-growing places in the United States. ⁠
⁠
Atascocita, in northeast Harris County, was the fifth fastest-growing place in the country from 2022 to 2023, according to a new analysis from SmartAsset, the personal finance website. Over the past five years, Atascocita's population has ballooned by nearly 40%, second only to Buckeye, Ariz. ⁠
⁠
Conroe, in Montgomery County, also made the top 10: It saw population growth of 6.73% from 2022 to 2023, the ninth-highest growth rate in the nation. Over the past five years, Conroe's population has grown by almost 25%. ⁠
⁠
Click the link in our bio to read more.⁠
⁠
📝: Erica Grieder / Houston Chronicle reporter

Police have described the attack in New Orleans as intentional, and said the truck's driver opened fired on police after the crash at approximately 3:15 a.m., wounding two officers. The driver, identified as Shamsud-Din Jabbar, 42, was killed in a shooting, according to the FBI.⁠
⁠
Just after 4 p.m., a tactical team made up of FBI agents and Harris County Sheriff's Office deputies rolled up to the property at the intersection Crescent Peak Drive and Hugh Road, in north Harris County.⁠
⁠
The property is believed to be where Jabbar lived in Houston.⁠
⁠
Police were flying a drone over the property, and carried long guns with them. At 4:20 p.m., a member of the team got on a loud speaker and told someone inside a building on the property to come out with their hands up.⁠
⁠
Click the link in our bio for live updates on the investigation. ⁠
⁠
📝: Megan Menchaca, John Wayne Ferguson, Matt deGrood / Houston Chronicle reporters⁠
📸: @melissaphillip713 / Houston Chronicle photographer⁠

At least 10 people are dead and dozens more injured after a Houston-area man drove a truck into a crowd in the French Quarter of New Orleans, authorities said.⁠
⁠
Federal law enforcement described the attack as intentional. The driver, identified as 42-year-old Shamsud-Din Jabbar of Houston, wounded two officers when he opened fire on police after the crash around 3:15 a.m. The driver was killed in a shooting, according to the FBI.⁠
⁠
Click the link in our bio for live updates on the investigation. ⁠
⁠
📝: Matt DeGrood / Houston Chronicle staff writer

One hundred twenty years ago today, Houston residents chose to end the ward system, a way of governance that had divided the city into six wards and ruled Houston since its founding days.⁠
⁠
Thus, the six wards as administrative boundaries were abolished, ushering in a precursor to what is now a 16-member City Council that includes 11 representatives from geographic districts, five at-large members and a mayor.⁠
⁠
But the wards live on as the names of some of Houston’s most iconic neighborhoods and communities of color, from Fifth Ward north of downtown to Third Ward south of it. ⁠
⁠
Click the link in our bio to read how these areas got these designations and why voters took the city down another path 120 years ago.⁠
⁠
✍️: Jhair Romero / Houston Chronicle reporter
📸: Gary Coronado, Johnny Hanson, Houston Public Library, @raquelnatalicchio

Oily skin presents as a shiny surface with enlarged pores, breakouts and blackheads. It requires deep cleansing and gentle hydration with reparative products to achieve healthy and radiant skin. ✨⁠
⁠
The featured skincare routine works to treat and prevent breakouts and is tailored specifically to problematic skin.⁠
⁠
- Start with Balancing Cleansing Gel, a non-foaming, oil-free anti-inflammatory cleanser which will help minimise the spread of bacteria on the skin.⁠
⁠
- Prep the skin with Rose Blossom Hydrating Mist, the perfect mist to balance PH levels and minimise pores.⁠
⁠
- Apply 2 drops of our Vital A Elixir (yes you can use this one during the day!) gently onto the face, neck and décolletage and allow actives Retinal & Bakuchiol to work on increasing cell turnover and reduce clogged pores.⁠
⁠
- Soothe, calm and balance oily skin with our light, refreshing Aloe Vera moisturiser. Not only can aloe vera reduce the swelling and redness associated with breakouts, it is also an antibacterial agent, meaning it can help address both the symptoms and the cause of breakouts.⁠
⁠
- Apply 1 pump of the Blemish Control directly to blemishes and allow to dry. This will help to remove excess oil, instantly soothing and calming flare ups. ⁠
⁠
- Lastly, sunscreen. Sun exposure can increase inflammation in the skin, which can worsen acne or trigger breakouts. Sunscreen helps protect against UV damage, reducing inflammation and keeping acne from flaring up.⁠
⁠

✨ Why Gua Sha deserves a place in your routine ✨⁠
⁠
If you’re looking for a simple, calming way to elevate your skincare game, perhaps it’s time you Gua Sha! ⁠
⁠
Gua Sha originated in ancient China as a traditional healing technique that dates back over 2,000 years and was initially used as a body treatment with the aim of promoting health, relieving pain and balancing the body’s internal energies. ⁠
⁠
The word “Gua” means “to scrape,” and “Sha” refers to the temporary red/purple spots that may appear after the scraping - which is believed to be an indicator of stagnant blood being released. This “Sha” was thought to clear out stagnation, support the body’s natural detox process and stimulate healing.⁠
⁠
In recent years, Gua Sha has been adapted as a gentler technique for the face, where it’s used to stimulate blood flow, support lymphatic drainage and encourage a natural lift. The facial version is much more delicate, without the deep scraping, and focuses on gentle gliding movements with the stone of your choice.⁠
⁠
Here are some of the many benefits:⁠
⁠
✨Sculpt and tone - Regular Gua Sha use helps naturally sculpt, lift, and tone facial muscles. Think of it as a gentle, rejuvenating workout for your face.⁠
⁠
✨Promotes lymphatic drainage - One of the most powerful benefits of Gua Sha is its ability to aid lymphatic drainage. By gently moving the tool along your skin in specific patterns, you’re supporting your lymphatic system, which removes toxins and excess fluid, helping to reduce puffiness.⁠
⁠
✨Boosts circulation - The gentle, gliding motion stimulates blood flow, which brings fresh nutrients to your skin, brightening and revitalising your complexion for that sought-after glow.⁠
⁠
✨Relieves muscle tension - Gua Sha is amazing for relieving tension in the face and neck, especially in the jawline, brow area, and temples. It’s like a mini massage that not only relaxes your muscles but also relieves stress and tension.⁠
⁠

Why choose retinal over retinol? 💛⁠
⁠
When it comes to achieving radiant, youthful skin, retinal (aka retinaldehyde) is the unsung hero of the retinoid family. Here’s why it deserves a spot in your skincare routine:⁠
⁠
✨ Faster results: Retinol needs to go through two conversions in your skin before it becomes active retinoic acid (the powerhouse that boosts cell turnover and collagen production). Retinal, however, is only one step away from retinoic acid, making it more direct and efficient. Translation? You’ll see results like smoother texture, reduced fine lines and a brighter complexion faster than with retinol.⁠
⁠
✨ Gentle yet effective: While retinal is more potent than retinol, it’s still gentle on the skin. It delivers transformative benefits without the irritation often associated with stronger retinoids, making it perfect for those who want results without the redness or peeling.⁠
⁠
✨ Powerful against acne & ageing: Retinal doesn’t just target wrinkles and dullness—it’s also a secret weapon against acne. Its antibacterial properties help reduce breakouts while keeping your skin balanced and healthy.⁠
⁠
✨ Future-proof your skin: By boosting collagen production and increasing cell turnover more efficiently, retinal helps prevent the signs of ageing before they even start. Think of it as your skin’s overachieving best friend.⁠
⁠
If you’re ready for faster, gentler, and more powerful results, it’s time to upgrade your routine to retinal!

گلایه گزارشگرمنوتو از وضعیت استادیوم آریامهر «آزادی»

پایگاه خبری اکسیوس به ��قل از سه منبع آگاه گزارش داد که جیک سالیوان، مشاور امنیت ملی کاخ سفید، در جلسه‌ای که چند هفته پیش برگزار شد، گزینه‌هایی برای حمله احتمالی ایالات متحده به تأسیسات هسته‌ای در ایران به رئیس‌جمهوری آمریکا، جو بایدن ارائه کرد.
بر اساس این گزارش، این جلسه حدود یک ماه پیش برگزار شد بایدن و جیک سالیوان، مشاور امنیت ملی کاخ سفید، گزینه‌های و سناریوهای مختلفی را بررسی کردند، اما رئیس‌ جمهوری آمریکا در آن جلسه تصمیمی نهایی نگرفت. هدف آن بررسی «سناریوهای احتیاطی» در صورت غنی‌سازی ۹۰ درصدی اورانیوم توسط جمهوری اسلامی تا پیش از ۲۰ ژانویه، آخرین روز حضور بایدن در کاخ سفید، بوده است.
اکسیوس همچنین به نقل از یک منبع مطلع نوشته است که موضوع حمله نظامی به تأسیسات هسته‌ای جمهوری اسلامی فعلاً در دستور کار کاخ سفید قرار ندارد.
مقام‌های رسمی ایالات متحده هنوز واکنشی به این گزارش نشان نداده‌اند.

مستند «ایران دهه پنجاه» 
‏به زودی تاریخ شروع پخش آزمایشی منوتو و این مستند اعلام می‌شود.
‏منوتو فراتر از سرگرمی

معاون فنی و نظارت سازمان نوسازی، توسعه و تجهیز مدارس کشور از شناسایی بیش از ۱۱۰۰ مدرسه سنگی در مناطق مختلف کشور خبر داد.
به گزارش رسانه‌های داخلی، مجید عبداللهی با اشاره به شناسایی اولیه این مدارس بر اساس فهرست‌های موجود گفت: «تلاش می‌شود با مشارکت مردم و حضور خیرین مدرسه‌ساز، بازسازی و جایگزینی این مدارس به سرعت انجام شود.»
این در حالی است که بسیاری از مناطق جنوبی ایران با بحران‌های جدی آموزشی روبه‌رو هستند. کمبود امکانات، فرسودگی مدارس، و نبود کلاس‌های درس از مشکلاتی است که دانش‌آموزان این مناطق با آن مواجه‌اند.

رسانه‌ حزب‌الله گزارش داد که مسافران یک پرواز از تهران به بیروت، هنگام ورود به فرودگاه رفیق حریری، تحت بازرسی شدید بدنی و بررسی غیرمعمول چمدان‌ها قرار گرفته‌اند.
بر اساس گزارش شبکه المنار، این بازرسی مربوط به یک هواپیمای متعلق به شرکت هواپیمایی ماهان‌ایر بوده است. همچنین گفته شده است که یک کارمند سفارت جمهوری اسلامی ایران از بازرسی کیف دیپلماتیک همراه خود ممانعت کرده و در سالن ورود مسافران فرودگاه تحت نظر قرار دارد.

سخنگوی اورژانس پیش‌بیمارستانی اهواز از وقوع تصادفی در نزدیکی روستای بارانگرد در محور ایذه-قلعه‌تل خبر داد.
عارف اصل شرهانی سخنگوی اورژانس اهواز اعلام کرد که این تصادف بین یک خودروی پژو ۴۰۵ و یک تریلر امروز حوالی قبرستان روستای بارانگرد رخ داده است.
او در ادامه گفت: در این حادثه پنج نفر مصدوم شدند که توسط دو دستگاه آمبولانس به بیمارستان شهید طباطبایی باغملک منتقل شدند

.
شرکت عربستانی تولید مواد غذایی «صافولا» که در تولید روغن‌های خوراکی در ایران سرمایه‌گذاری کرده بود، کل دارایی‌ خود در ایران را به ارزش ۷۰۵ میلیون ریال عربستان (معادل ۱۸۸ میلیون دلار) فروخته و از کشور خارج می‌شود. براساس بیانیه‌ای که گروه صافولا روز چهارشنبه ۱۲ دی‌ماه منتشر کرد، تصمیم برای توقف فعالیت این شرکت در ایران «در راستای استراتژی گروه برای خروج به‌موقع از بازارهای غیراصلی» اتخاذ شده است.
گروه صافولا که بزرگ‌ترین سرمایه‌گذار سعودی‌ در ایران به شمار می‌رفت، در تولید روغن‌های خوراکی شامل لادن، لادن طلایی، بهار و نسترن سرمایه‌گذاری کرده بود. خبرگزاری تسنیم، نزدیک به سپاه پاسداران، در سال ۱۳۹۴ گزارش داد «صافولا ۴۰ درصد روغن مصرفی در ایران را تأمین می کند و همچنین مالکیت کامل شرکت شکر صافولا بهشر و شرکت توزیع‌کننده طلوع پخش آفتاب را در اختیار دارد».

دونالد ترامپ، رئیس‌جمهور منتخب ایالات متحده، با انتقاد شدید از سیاست‌های مهاجرتی جو بایدن، او را «بدترین رئیس‌جمهور تاریخ آمریکا» توصیف کرد.
دونالد ترامپ در حساب کاربری ایکس نوشت: «با سیاست مرزهای باز بایدن، بارها هشدار داده بودم که تروریسم اسلامی رادیکال و دیگر اشکال جنایت خشونت‌آمیز در آمریکا گسترش خواهند یافت. اکنون این هشدارها به حقیقت پیوسته و وضعیت حتی بدتر از تصورات شده است.»
وی افزود: «کارهایی که بایدن و تیمش، که آن‌ها را گروهی از اشرار و مداخله‌گران در انتخابات می‌نامم، با کشور ما انجام داده‌اند، به‌زودی فراموش نخواهد شد. او یک فاجعه کامل و تمام‌عیار است.»
ترامپ پیش‌تر نیز به‌طور مکرر از سیاست‌های مرزی و مهاجرتی دولت بایدن انتقاد کرده و آن‌ها را عامل افزایش ناامنی در آمریکا دانسته است.

بر اساس اعلام شرکت کنترل کیفیت هوای تهران، میانگین کیفیت هوای پایتخت در شرایط «ناسالم برای گروه‌های حساس» قرار دارد.
بر اساس این گزارش، علی‌رغم بارندگی در تهران، شاخص آلاینده هوای پایتخت در روز شنبه بر روی عدد ۱۱۸ قرار گرفته و کیفیت هوا در وضعیت ناسالم برای گروه‌های حساس است.
تهران از ابتدای سال ۵ روز هوای پاک، ۱۷۹ روز هوای قابل قبول و ۹۰ روز هوای ناسالم برای گروه‌های حساس و ۱۵ روز هوای ناسالم داشته است.

بنا بر گزارش پلیس فدرال آمریکا مردی که یک خودروی سایبرتراک تسلا را مقابل هتل بین‌المللی ترامپ در لاس‌وگاس منفجر کرد، سرباز ارتش آمریکا بوده و پیش از انفجار مواد منفجره داخل خودرو با شلیک گلوله خودکشی کرده بود.
به گفته مقامات این فرد، متیو لیولزبرگر، ۳۷ ساله، اهل کلرادو و یک سرباز نخبه ارتش آمریکا بود.
ویدئویی از لحظه انفجار یک خودروی تسلا سایبرتراک در مقابل برج ترامپ در رسانه ها منتشر شده است .

ویدئویی از سقوط یک هواپیمای کوچک روی پشت‌بام یک ساختمان تجاری در کالیفرنیا در رسانه‌های اجتماعی منتشر شده است.
در پی این حادثه دو نفر کشته و دست‌کم ۱۵ نفر زخمی شدند.

All of humanity is involved in a raging-neverending battle between good and evil, or what we simply call life. Fortunately, life is the sum of all your choices, and ultimately we are what we chose to be. Everything is a reflection of a choice you have made. Some choices we are proud of, some we regret, and some will haunt us forever.

New Jersey bar-barian, Purest Ghostin, emerges from the shadows with “Lights Out” to raise the curtain on everyone’s internal struggle to make the right choices and remain on the right side of spiritual warfare. The haunting-mesmerizing Sosick-produced backdrop perfectly connects Ghostin’s interdimensional wordplay, aiming at evil forces that seek to lure us all to the dark side or merely snuff out our flame. The G.I.FILMS cinematic visual perfectly documents the inner turmoil of actress Linda Wolfe, as she battles her life’s demons in an old sketchy motel. Purest Ghostin spoke about “Lights Out”, proclaiming, “These are the eternal battles we fight every second we are breathing and it is always the darkest before dawn, so I hope this radiates strength and perseverance to keep shining no matter what forces continue to extinguish your light. So will you shine or will it be lights out? Never give up. Keep fighting.”

“Lights Out” is out now on all platforms via GIDDT//AVM and is the latest release from Purest Ghostin’s forthcoming album “Paragraphs In Crimson”.

New case alert 🚨 

@advocates4faith is proud to represent 2 young female athletes in challenging policies that force them out to make room for biological male athletes. 

Our clients - high school cross-country runners at Marin Luther King High School in Riverside County- are standing firm after being told they are not permitted to wear shirts that read “Save Girls’ Sports” and “It’s Common Sense. XX ≠ XY”.

 “We will not allow boys to take over girls’ sports or let woke policies silence young women fighting for fair competition,” said Advocates attorney, Julianne Fleischer. “This case is about protecting equal opportunities and the freedom to speak out—values that should be upheld, not suppressed, in our schools.”

“I’m calling on President Trump and the incoming Congress to restore women’s sports and to stop the mockery of women by this radical and ignorant ideology,” stated Advocates attorney, Robert Tyler.

Embrace a clear mind and uplifted spirit this Dry January with our herbal-infused mocktail, Chakra Khan! 🌱🧠✨

Infused with our classic CBD honey and compassion from the heart chakra, this herbal mocktail not only supports your wellness journey but also brings a refreshed perspective on self-love. Try at home and with loved ones. Cheers to a healthier, brighter you!

Ingredients: 
- Mint leaves 
- Lemons 
- Limes 
- Sweets CBD honey and cucumber mint simple syrup
- Cucumber pineapple juice 
- CQ blackberry lemon lime-infused spritzer (or seltzer)
- Thin cucumber slices 
- Ice cubes

Method: 
Add mint leaves, fresh lemons, and limes to your shaker. Muddle it all together to combine. Add 4oz of our homemade CBD Honey Cucumber mint simple syrup. 
Add 2 oz of cucumber and pineapple juice. Add ice, secure the shaker lid, and shake 
In the drinking glass, add cucumber slices and ice cubes. Pour the mixture over the ice and top with @cq_drinks CQ BlackBerry Lemon Lime infused spritzer (or a seltzer of your choice)
Garnish with mint leaves and folded cucumber slices, and enjoy!

Put the lighter away🔥

Newer furnaces (since about 2010) typically don’t have pilot lights, but instead use an electronic ignition system. 

This is because standing pilot lights waste energy by constantly burning gas to keep the flame lit. 

If you have a newer fuenace, you can try resetting the electronic ignition by turning it off and then pressing the reset button.

Here are some other things you can try if your furnace isn’t turning on: 

-Check thermostat batteries
-Check for a tripped circuit breaker
-Check that furnace power is switched on
-Check if the filter is dirty

Gas is dangerous and poking around with a lighter could end badly😬 Be sure you know what you’re doing when lighting an older furnace pilot light (look up furnace model online for directions for your specific furnace)

***DON’T WORRY*** In the winter when heat pumps run in “heat” mode, they drain condensation from the outdoor unit and, if it’s cold enough, it will form ice. 

The system can sense if it has ice on it and will go into “defrost mode”. 

You’ll end up with a puddle and it looks like a leak or a problem—but it’s TOTALLY NORMAL! 

This is one of the reasons heat pumps are installed up on a base, so they can drain in the winter. #themoreyouknow

What does it mean for "colorless green ideas [to] sleep furiously"? 🌱💤

Well … nothing. That is the point. In 1957, linguist Noam Chomsky introduced the now-famous sentence "Colorless green ideas sleep furiously" as part of his groundbreaking work in linguistics.

The sentence is meant to illustrate the distinction between syntax (sentence structure) and semantics (sentence meaning). While the sentence follows the grammatical rules of English, it does not make sense conceptually.

Since Chomsky wrote it, there have been attempts to make sense of the sentence. In 1985, a literary competition was held at Stanford University in which the contestants were invited to make Chomsky's sentence meaningful using not more than 100 words of prose or 14 lines of verse.

The nonsense quality of the sentence has also been used in research on social manners and conversation. In one study, scientists inserted the meaningless sentence 8 minutes into real conversations to test reactions. After the conversation, the participants did a questionnaire, mainly asking if they thought the conversation was unusual. The study found evidence that people tend to ignore the inconsistency of speech to protect the quality of a conversation.

Have any ideas of your own about what the sentence could mean? Read more at the link in our bio.

Did you know that dolphins and sea lions have been trained for military purposes? ⚓

Military programs in the United States and the Soviet Union trained these animals for tasks such as:
🐬 Mine detection: Dolphins use their echolocation to locate underwater mines, providing safer alternatives to traditional methods.
🐬 Object retrieval: Sea lions are trained to retrieve equipment lost at sea, thanks to their excellent eyesight and dexterity.
🐬Harbor defense: Both dolphins and sea lions assist in guarding harbors by detecting and intercepting intruders, including divers or unmanned vehicles.

The use of military marine mammals raises ethical questions. While their abilities are impressive, concerns about their welfare are frequently voiced. 

Dive into this topic at the link in our bio.

What if time moved slower the closer you were to a big object? Or if space itself could bend and ripple like a fabric? These are just some of the mind-bending ideas at the heart of Albert Einstein’s theory of general relativity. 

But relativity is not the easiest concept to understand. This is where Wikipedia shines. The “Introduction to general relativity” article is designed for readers seeking a conceptual understanding without diving into advanced mathematics or physics. It introduces key concepts like spacetime curvature, gravitational waves, and black holes in clear, approachable language.

The article incorporates diagrams, simplified explanations, and real-world examples — like how general relativity predicts the bending of light around massive objects (gravitational lensing) — to illustrate abstract ideas. It is a featured article, meaning the Wikipedia community of editors have voted to name it among the best the free encyclopedia has to offer.

For those ready to dig deeper, Wikipedia provides links to related articles that tackle advanced topics like Einstein field equations or differential geometry. This layered approach ensures that both beginners and experts find value.

General relativity underpins GPS technology, shapes our understanding of the universe, and continues to inspire scientific discovery. Wikipedia ensures that such groundbreaking concepts are not confined to textbooks or academic journals, but are available to curious minds worldwide, regardless of their educational background.

Speedrunning is the act of playing a video game, or section of a video game, with the goal of completing it as fast as possible.

Understanding and exploiting the mechanics behind a game requires extensive research, technical knowledge, and an incredible level of precision. Speedrunners essentially reverse-engineer games to uncover the inner workings of their code. Where traditional gameplay focuses on narrative or leisurely enjoyment, speedrunning dives into the technical depths of what makes a game tick.

The roots of speedrunning can be traced back to the early days of arcade gaming, but it began gaining traction in the late 1990s. One of the earliest examples was the community that played “Doom”, which established the groundwork for modern speedrunning. Players shared "demo" recordings of their fastest runs, fostering a culture of competition and collaboration. 

Today, speedrunners often share their “runs” through platforms like Twitch and YouTube. Competitions also act to help grow the modern community. 

One of the most prominent aspects of speedrunning is the use of glitches — intentional or accidental quirks in a game’s programming. Though there are many “glitchless” competitions as well, speedrunners often exploit glitches to bypass obstacles, skip large portions of a game, or even manipulate the game’s code to achieve impossibly fast times. 

Speedrunning combines skill, precision, and creativity to achieve the fastest runs possible. To learn more about this world, check out the link in our bio.

In most of medieval Europe, a system called feudalism defined one's status in life. Local rulers known as lords controlled the land, and everyone who lived on it – peasants, farmers, and even knights – owed taxes, labor, or military service in return for protection. This system of hierarchy structured nearly every aspect of society, with common people at the bottom.

But in the north of the Netherlands and parts of northwestern Germany, the Frisians lived differently.

Frisian lands existed in a state of autonomy from at least the 11th century, governing themselves without the rule of feudal lords. Known today as Frisian freedom, this unusual arrangement allowed the population to make decisions through communal assemblies, guided by customary laws. They acknowledged powerful overarching rulers like the Holy Roman Emperor, but avoided the daily control and obligations typically imposed by local feudal overlords. The Frisian nobility that did exist during this time never developed feudal titles. 

This was rare on a continent with widespread feudalism and arose from specific historical and geographic circumstances. It was also fragile. By the mid-14th century, local military chieftains had grown more rich and powerful, developing into an aristocracy that reduced the role of communal decision-making. Internal conflicts and external pressures from neighboring powers eventually ended Frisian freedom by the late 15th century. By the modern period, the Frisian freedom became a national myth, assuming a continuous history of Frisian independence that lasted for over eight centuries, and the concept was subjected to increased simplification and commodification.

Read about the rise and fall of this unusual society at the link in our bio.

🧬 Evolution is known as survival of the fittest. But sometimes, getting along is the most clever survival strategy of all. 

Explore the science behind reciprocal altruism, a behavior where individuals help one another with an expectation of future reciprocation ⬇️

Developed in evolutionary biology, this concept describes how animals (and humans) engage in actions that benefit others, confident that support will be returned over time. The cleaner fish and its host, or vampire bats that share food, are well-known examples where cooperation enhances survival.

This form of mutual aid mirrors human solidarity, where reciprocal actions foster trust and unity in societies. 

Read more about the possible evolutionary basis of human cooperation at the link in our bio.

1992. This year marked a decisive shift in our advertising strategy. Instead of taking the pictures himself, Toscani selected seven photographs taken by journalists to document some of the most pressing social issues of the time, simply adding the United Colors of Benetton logo to them. Shot in black and white by photographer Therese Frare and later colorized, this particular image shows David Kirby, a US HIV/AIDS activist and patient, surrounded by his family on his deathbed. Displayed in newspapers and on billboards around the world, the advertisement sparked a global controversy: many criticized us and called for a boycott, while others saw it as a way to raise awareness about the AIDS epidemic and encourage action from political elites. When later asked about his perspective, Kirby’s father said: "Benetton didn’t use us, or exploit us. We used them. Because of them, [David’s] photo was seen all over the world, and that’s exactly what David wanted."

@olivierotoscanistudio

1990. Two toddlers sitting on two potties, looking at each other. An apparently innocent image, yet one that was interpreted and criticized in countless ways, like many of Toscani’s campaigns for our brand. The Archbishop and the Municipality of Milan stopped Benetton from displaying the advertisement on a massive billboard (770 square meters) in Piazza del Duomo, citing the need to protect the sensibilities of churchgoers. During Toscani’s years, our campaigns were rejected by several magazines and censored for various reasons in countries such as Saudi Arabia, Norway, the Netherlands, the Vatican, Japan, the United States, Germany, France, and the UK.

@olivierotoscanistudio

1985. Toscani took the idea of a united world to the next level in this campaign, which depicts pairs of children holding flags from different, often opposing nations, such as Israel and Palestine, Greece and Turkey, Argentina and the UK. This image in particular is part of a series focusing on the conflict between the USA and the USSR, which suggested and, in a way, predicted the end of the Cold War. When Mikhail Gorbachev visited Paris on a diplomatic trip in 1985, Toscani decided to cover the Champs-Élysées with images of two children - one holding a USSR flag and the other holding a USA flag - kissing each other. Legend has it that the Soviet president was struck by the billboards and asked his collaborators, "Who is Benetton?"

@olivierotoscanistudio

#Benetton

2017. This is one of the last campaigns Toscani shot for us. A classroom of 28 kids, coming from 13 nations and 4 continents, in a school near Milan. “The main issue today is integration,” Toscani said at the time. “The future will depend on how and how well we use our intelligence to integrate the different, overcoming our fears.” 

@olivierotoscanistudio

2000. The "We, on Death Row" campaign aimed to raise awareness about the death penalty. Toscani visited several U.S. prisons and photographed some men who had been sentenced to death. The images were published on billboards, in newspapers and magazines, as well as in a catalog. Once again, they sparked strong reactions, both in favor of and against United Colors of Benetton and Toscani.

@olivierotoscanistudio

1984. The beginning of the collaboration between Toscani and United Colors of Benetton. Oliviero photographs groups of children and young people from different ethnic backgrounds, dressed in Benetton clothing, against a white background. Our brand’s colorful sweaters become a metaphor for a utopian society, where individual differences are celebrated and tolerance is widespread. Some of these early campaigns feature the slogan “Tutti i colori del mondo,” Italian for “all the colors of the world", which would later evolve into the brand’s name: United Colors of Benetton.

@olivierotoscanistudio

Oliviero Toscani (1942-2025) was a creative force that changed forever the role that advertising plays in the public debate. In the gallery above, we celebrate him with some of the most thought-provoking, iconic campaigns he shot for United Colors of Benetton.

@olivierotoscanistudio

From the adv images celebrating diversity and freedom of expression to the projects raising awareness about AIDS and the death penalty, all the way to the legendary COLORS Magazine, Oliviero Toscani’s work for United Colors of Benetton had the power to turn corporate communications into a tool for social and cultural change.

@olivierotoscanistudio

The U.S. Supreme Court on Friday (Jan. 17) upheld a federal statute that will effectively ban TikTok from the country, rejecting the company’s arguments that the law violates the First Amendment.⁠
⁠
The unanimous ruling, citing national security concerns about China's control over the popular app, is set to go in effect on Sunday due to the U.S. government's fears about China’s control over TikTok.⁠
⁠
“There is no doubt that, for more than 170 million Americans, TikTok offers a distinctive and expansive outlet for expression, means of engagement, and source of community,” the justices wrote. “But Congress has determined that divestiture is necessary to address its well-supported national security concerns regarding TikTok’s data collection practices and relationship with a foreign adversary.”⁠
⁠
More details are at the link in bio.

Bob Dylan’s solo music catalog has been surging in streams thanks to the new biopic ‘A Complete Unknown.’

Just hours after the Recording Academy announced that it plans to go ahead with the 67th annual Grammy Awards telecast on Feb. 2 as scheduled despite the wildfires that have devastated parts of Los Angeles in the past week, Universal Music Group announced it is canceling all of the company’s Grammy-related events, including its artist showcase and after-Grammy party.
⁠
Instead, UMG will "redirect the resources that would have been used for those events to assist those affected by the wildfires."⁠
⁠
Warner Music Group also confirmed to Billboard that the company made a decision over the weekend not to hold a Grammy Week party and will instead redirect funds to efforts to combat the wildfires and help those affected by the destruction.⁠
⁠
More details at the link in bio.

When it comes to bringing back country music's old-school sound, @zachtop says "three chords and the truth are necessary."

"A fiddle and steel guitar never hurt," he adds. "But it’s songs that make people feel something and something that’s got a story to it. That’s what I love about country music — songs that make me feel understood, no matter what stage of life I’m in.”

He chats through his music-making process, inspirations and more in his Billboard digital exclusive Genre Now cover story.

An ex-gang leader is seeking to have all the charges against him dismissed in the 1990s killing of rap music icon Tupac Shakur.⁠
⁠
Attorney Carl Arnold filed the motion on Monday in the District Court of Nevada to dismiss charges against Duane Davis in the 1996 shooting of Shakur. The motion alleges “egregious” constitutional violations because of a 27-year delay in prosecution. The motion also asserts a lack of corroborating evidence and failure to honor immunity agreements granted to Davis by federal and local authorities.⁠
⁠
“The prosecution has failed to justify a decades-long delay that has irreversibly prejudiced my client,” Arnold said in a news release. “Moreover, the failure to honor immunity agreements undermines the criminal justice system’s integrity and seriously questions this prosecution.”⁠
⁠

Five individuals have been charged in connection with the death of Liam Payne, the former One Direction singer who died Oct. 16 after falling from a hotel balcony in Buenos Aires, according to a public notice by Argentina‘s National Criminal and Correctional Prosecutor’s Office.⁠
⁠
Those charged include hotel manager Gilda Martin, receptionist Esteban Grassi, and Payne’s friend Roger Nores, all facing manslaughter charges. Additionally, hotel employee Ezequiel Pereyra and waiter Braian Paiz have been charged with supplying drugs. In Argentina’s legal system, prosecutors gather evidence for a judge to determine whether to proceed to trial. Judge Laura Bruniard has moved the case to the next stage, a decision the defendants’ lawyers may appeal. If the appeal fails, the case will proceed to trial.⁠
⁠
More details on the trail is at the link in bio.⁠

The woman who accused Jay-Z and Sean “Diddy” Combs of drugging and raping her when she was 13 years old can remain anonymous for now, a judge ruled, citing the “highly sensitive” nature of her accusations.

According to court documents obtained by Billboard, Judge Annalisa Torres wrote that “the weight of the factors” in the case “tips in favor of allowing Plaintiff to remain anonymous” for now. In justifying the decision, the judge cited the Jane Doe’s assertion that she continues to suffer from depression, post-traumatic stress disorder and other health effects due to the alleged rape, as well as a claim by the woman’s attorneys that Combs has threatened other alleged victims who have filed suits against him for speaking out. However, the judge acknowledges that “because the balance of these factors will certainly shift” as the case moves forward, she plans to revisit the question of anonymity at a later date.

Everything we know about the new ruling is at the link in bio.

These low-level factors are often present in the lives of many children at times.
Some behaviors are harmless, normal, or even beneficial for children.
Yet all of these behaviors and risk factors, when a certain adults relationship with a child includes several, are an indication to take a closer look: they are up to 3.5 times more likely to be present in child sexual abuse cases.

- Feeling needy
- Activities planned alone with a child or without other adults present
- Extra attention paid to a specific child
- Spending a lot of time or communicating often with a specific child
- Showing a specific child love or affection over the others
- Telling a child the adult loves them or that the child is special to them
- Showing favoritism or calling the relationship with a specific child 'special'
- Giving a child compliments often
- Seeming charming, nice, or likeable
- Inviting a child on overnight stays or outings outside or without the rest of the childs' family
- Giving a specific child special rewards or privileges
- Engaging in child-like activities with a child outside of the family
- Child experiences lower confidence or self-esteem
- Child is lonely or self-isolates
- Child experiences or exhibits psychological or behavioral trouble

#DoveMenPartner ”Dad” has always had a complicated meaning for me. Which is why I was so for this entire campaign @dovemencare is doing to expand the definition of fatherhood this year and celebrate all father figures who have stepped up in our lives. My biological Dad left when I was little and I haven’t seen him since. It left me with a lot of trauma and a lot of fear. My mom remarried when I was still pretty young and I gained a “step” dad. I use “step” in quotes because honestly I’ve never referred to him as that, he’s always just been “Dad” to me. Truthfully, our relationship hasn’t always been perfect, we’ve navigated hard things and I had to work through a lot of trust and abandonment issues. However, since my Mom passed away, he and I have grown closer, even if we are thousands of miles away. He’s always been the best Gaga to my babies, they adore him. He has stepped in and helped in more ways than I can even express, my entire life. And he CHOSE to be my Dad, even when it truthfully wasn’t his responsibility. So for Father’s Day this year, I hope we can remember that Dads come in all shapes and sizes, biological or not, step or not. I am so grateful for the impact my Dad has made in my life and for all he has and continues to do for me and my little family. Go check out the new Dove Men+Care film, Care Makes a Difference, in my story to see other stories like mine. #CareMakesADifference #CAREmakesaDAD

I’m excited to partner with @dovemencare this Father’s Day to celebrate & honor the many different types of father figures that pour into us. #DoveMenPartner I want to thank my high school football head coach Ajay Ulmer for seeing qualities in me that I never knew I possessed. The belief, support & unconditional care you showed me really shaped who I am today Coach. I’m forever grateful for all that you did for me & the guys.⁣
⁣
Thank you @dovemencare for allowing me to be a part of this wonderful moment. Check out the Dove Men+Care film in my story that celebrates how it’s care that makes a difference! #CareMakesADifference #CAREmakesaDAD #CelebrateALLDads

Did you know there are three common types of hair loss, each with unique causes? 

Understanding these can guide you toward the right treatment and solutions.

Telogen Effluvium: Often triggered by stress or sudden shocks, leading to noticeable shedding.

Androgenetic Alopecia: The most common form of hair loss, influenced by genetics, hormones, and aging.

Alopecia Areata: An autoimmune condition that causes patchy hair loss in round spots.

To precisely diagnose your hair loss condition, consult with a certified medical advisor, such as a trichologist or dermatologist. 

However, no matter the condition, Hairmax will help you tackle hair loss and regrow your confidence!

✨ Postpartum Hair Loss: You’re Not Alone ✨

Many new moms notice extra shedding in the months after giving birth, and while it can be surprising, it’s a normal part of recovery! Here’s what’s happening and how to support your hair on this journey 💕👇🏽:

During pregnancy, estrogen keeps your hair in a longer growth phase, giving you those extra-full locks. But after birth, hormones shift, leading to postpartum shedding. This typically starts 2-3 months after birth and can last several months.

💙 Nourish & Strengthen: Try gentle styles, focus on scalp care, and use nutrient-rich products to encourage healthy regrowth. Kurlee Belle’s Blu Renew Scalp Serum, Thirsty Kurls Leave-In Conditioner, and Banana Nut Deep Treatment were made with this in mind! 💧🌱

Remember, this phase is temporary, and your hair will soon return to its natural cycle. Treat your strands with extra care and give yourself grace through this process 💪🏽💫 Shop now at kurleebelle.com.

5 Ways to Apply Gel to Elongate Curls ✨

1️⃣ Rake Method – Apply gel to damp hair and use your fingers to rake the gel through each section, stretching the curls as you go. This ensures even distribution while elongating the curl pattern.

2️⃣ Shingling Method – Work in small sections, applying gel generously and smoothing it down each curl with your fingers. This method helps to elongate and define each curl individually.

3️⃣ Praying Hands Method – Smooth gel over your curls by pressing your hands together like you're praying, stretching the curls downward as you apply to elongate them.

4️⃣ Banding Method – After applying gel, divide your hair into sections and secure each section with hair bands along the length of the hair. This stretches the curls while the gel sets, helping to elongate them.

5️⃣ Finger Coil and Stretch – Twist small sections of hair around your fingers to define the curls, then gently pull the ends to stretch the curl pattern as the gel dries.

🚫 Are you making these mistakes that could be causing low porosity hair?

1️⃣ Overuse of Heavy Products
Too many thick creams, oils, or butters can create a barrier, making it hard for moisture to penetrate. Try Kurlee Tropical Oils Blend for a lighter, nourishing touch! 🌿

2️⃣ Incorrect Use of Protein Treatments
Too much protein can make your hair rigid. Balance it out with our Honey Ginger Protein Deep Treatment – perfect for strengthening without overloading! 🍯

3️⃣ Skipping Heat Treatments
Deep conditioning without heat can prevent moisture from absorbing. Use Thirsty Kurls Leave-in Conditioner with heat to ensure moisture gets locked in! 💧

4️⃣ Using Cold Water to Wash Hair
Cold water can block moisture from entering. Rinse with Mango Guava Conditioner for soft, shiny hair! 🍈✨

5️⃣ Frequent Use of Silicones & Mineral Oils
These can cause buildup, leading to low porosity hair. Choose Papaya Avocado Curl Milk for a silicone-free, nourishing experience! 🥑

Keep your hair hydrated & healthy with the right routine! ✨💆🏽‍♀️
